JPMorgan Chase, American Express share losses lead Dow's 750-point fall

Shares of JPMorgan Chase and American Express are seeing declines Friday morning, leading the Dow Jones Industrial Average slump. Shares of JPMorgan Chase JPM, +0.65% and American Express AXP, -0.57% have contributed to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 755 points (2.9%) lower. JPMorgan Chase's shares have fallen $5.66, or 5.0%, while those of American Express have fallen $5.45 (4.9%), combining for a roughly 75-point drag on the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the decline are Home Depot HD, -0.03%, Coca-Cola KO, +0.12%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.48%. A $1 move in any of the Dow's 30 components equates to a 6.78-point swing.

